{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/machine-learning-101-id3-decision-trees-and-entropy-calculation-1-a1d66ee9f728", "time": 1683001296.0875351, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/machine-learning-101-id3-decision-trees-and-entropy-calculation-1-a1d66ee9f728/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Machine Learning 101-ID3 Decision Tree and Entropy Calculation (1) | by ay\u015fe bilge g\u00fcnd\u00fcz | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Machine Learning 101-ID3 Decision Tree and Entropy Calculation (1)", "description": "Entropy known as the controller for decision tree to decide where to split the data. ID3 algorithm uses entropy to calculate the homogeneity of a sample. If the sample is completely homogeneous the\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [], "all_paragraphs": ["Machine Learning training approaches divide into 3;", "Entropy known as the controller for decision tree to decide where to split the data. ID3 algorithm uses entropy to calculate the homogeneity of a sample. If the sample is completely homogeneous the entropy is zero and if the sample is an equally divided it has entropy of one[1].", "p\u2082 = 5/14 (probability of a sample in the same training class with class 2)", "The boundaries of root, nodes and leaves are defined by Information Gain (IG).", "Note: You can find ID3 as C4.5 in WEKA Tool.", "First, select the feature that will divide the whole table in the most accurate way. For this, the feature that gives the highest gain should be determined.Values for 10 training examples are divided as follows:* 6 Cinema* 2 Tennis* 1 House* 1 ShoppingEntropy value must be calculated from these values for the beginning to define root feature.", "By calculating the gain values of all individual features, the features with the highest gain value is selected as the root node:", "Finally, all gain values are listed one by one and the feature with the highest gain value is selected as the root node. In this case weather has the highest gain value so It will be the root.", "As shown in the above example, after selecting the root, each of the individual values of the features are determined as leaves and this time the data set is customized with these individual values. In other words, the table above has been converted to a separate data set showing the values that other features can take if the weather is Sunny. Thus, when the weather is sunny, according to this table, the possible classes of the inter node will be as follow:", "Because the gain of the Parental_Availability feature is greater, the leaf of the Sunny state will be Parental_Availability. According to the data set for sunny conditions, if yes, Cinema will be decided and if no, then Tennis will be decided:", "When the same calculations are made for Windy and Rainy situations, the final decision tree will be completed.", "In order to avoid overfitting, it is necessary to prun the tree either when it is growing or after the tree is formed.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "MLE @ Quantcast, PhD student in Computer Science, Fan of Data Science and Cyber Security"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fa1d66ee9f728&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmachine-learning-101-id3-decision-trees-and-entropy-calculation-1-a1d66ee9f728&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fmachine-learning-101-id3-decision-trees-and-entropy-calculation-1-a1d66ee9f728&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"